sec.p:
Couples’ perceived access to peer support was the independent variable of interest and, for this analysis, was conceptualised by self-rated strength of agreement with two statements describing friendships outside of the primary partnership. The statements were adapted from a standardised scale measuring sense of autonomy within the relationship [42], and translated into isiZulu:
‘I have a supportive group of friends separate from my partner’ (‘friends’ score);
‘I have a close friend other than my partner’ (‘close friend’ score).
